subSubSection.paragraph:
Variation.
Males, measurements in mm (n= 11, including the 
holotype
): TL 1.58–1.78 (1.67 ± 0.07), PL 0.55– 0.68 (0.62 ± 0.04), PW 0.63–0.70 (0.67 ± 0.02), EL 0.95–1.18 (1.05 ± 0.07), EW 0.65–0.75 (0.71 ± 0.03), GD 0.63–0.70 (0.65 ± 0.04), PL/PW 0.85–1.00 (0.93 ± 0.05), EL/EW 1.36–1.59 (1.48 ± 0.07), EL/PL 1.41–1.96 (1.70 ± 0.18), GD/EW 0.88–0.93 (0.91 ± 0.02), TL/EW 2.23–2.43 (2.36 ± 0.06). In some males, the pronotal plates are short (
Fig. 19
) or the plate of head is short and pronotal edge is rounded (
Figs 20–21
). Females, measurements in mm (n= 10): TL 1.45–1.73 (1.63 ± 0.08), PL 0.53–0.63 (0.58 ± 0.06), PW 0.55–0.70 (0.64 ± 0.05), EL 1.00–1.10 (1.05 ± 0.04), EW 0.63–0.78 (0.70 ± 0.05), GD 0.58–0.70 (0.65 ± 0.04), PL/PW 0.82–1.00 (0.91 ± 0.05), EL/EW 1.37–1.68 (1.50 ± 0.10), EL/PL 1.64–2.22 (1.82 ± 0.17), GD/EW 0.83–0.97 (0.93 ± 0.05), TL/EW 2.13–2.52 (2.32 ± 0.11). In both males and females, coloration can range from reddish brown to reddish dark brown. In specimens from 
Guatemala
the pronotal punctation is slightly sparser than in the Mexican specimens.
